# Fixture: fm11-bind-scoping
# Finding: BIND variable scoping — ?x defined by BIND must not appear
#          in the same group graph pattern before the BIND.
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 §18.2.1 (variable scoping in group graph patterns)
#
# Hypothesis: SPARQL §18.2.1 states that a variable introduced by BIND
# must not already appear in the group graph pattern up to that point.
# The fixture below uses ?x in a triple pattern AFTER the BIND that
# defines it — legal. A second fixture uses ?x BEFORE the BIND — which
# is a grammar/semantic violation and must be rejected.
#
# Divergence: An implementation that accepts ?x before a BIND that also
# defines ?x violates §18.2.1. This fixture tests the *legal* form;
# the illegal form is in fm11b.
# Grammar-level behaviour: parses successfully.

SELECT * WHERE {
  ?s <http://example/p> ?o .
  BIND(CONCAT(STR(?o), "-suffix") AS ?x)
  ?s <http://example/q> ?x .
}
